<p>
Dimensioned quaternions. Hamilton's numbers of the form a + bi + cj + dk with a unit of measurement.
</p>
<p>
Quaternions have homogeneous units of measurement. In a quaternion of type <code>Quaternion(a)</code> the 
scalar part has unit <code>a</code> and the vector part has unit <code>a*Geom3!</code>.
</p>
